  "text": "AQ is an automated online technique that analyzes the ultrasound backscatter to identify the blood-tissue interface of cardiac chambers and generate volume waveforms within a defined region of interest [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The automated border detection system is activated and optimized by adjusting the total and lateral gain and temporal gain compensation. The AQ-derived instantaneous volume in volume over time waveforms is displayed together with the electrocardiography tracing.",
